      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">The Components in the UPS Principle Diagram</title>
         <table pgwide="1" class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="9.99%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="29.72%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="41.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">Component</entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">Explanation</entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">X001</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Rectifier mains terminal</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This terminal provides for the connection of the rectifier
mains (L1, L2, L3, PE).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T001</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Option: Rectifier mains transfomer</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Matches the rectifier mains voltage to the correct value for
the rectifier, and provides galvanic isolation.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q001</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Rectifier mains
input switch</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This switch ensures
isolation of the rectifier mains input (no trip function).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">K101</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Input
backfeed contactor</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Power_Connection_Board_A101_REF_0000103189.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A101</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Power connection
board</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Power_Connection_Board_A101_REF_0000103189.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A102</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Controller box</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Controller_Box_A102_REF_0000103188.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T101 — T102</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Power modules</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Power_Module_T101_T102_REF_0000102069.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">X201</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Battery terminal</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This terminal ensures the connection of the battery positive
pole (B+) and the negative pole (B-).</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q201</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Battery switch</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q401</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Static bypass switch (Thyristors)</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Static_Bypass_Switch_Module_SBS_REF_0000103119.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A401</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Static bypass switch controller</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_SBS_Controller_A401_REF_0000103064.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T401</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Option: Inverter output transformer</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This transformer galvanically isolates the load from the battery
and adapts the output voltage to the required voltage of the inverter
power module. No transformer is used, if no galvanic isolation is
required, and if the required output voltage is in the range from
380–415 V for 3–phase system and 220–240 V for
1–phase systems.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">X501</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Bypass mains input terminal</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This terminal provides for the connection of the bypass mains:
1, 2, or 3 phases, neutral and ground, dependent on the configuration
and type. For 3–phase systems one common set of terminals for
rectifier and bypass mains is possible.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q501</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Bypass mains input switch</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This switch isolates the bypass mains input.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">T501</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Option: Bypass
mains input transformer</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This component
provides for the galvanic isolation between the bypass mains input
and the load. It can also be installed in the case of a different
bypass mains input voltage and output voltage. A stabilizer can be
installed instead of a transformer.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q528</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Bypass
mains input switch</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Provides
for the isolation of the bypass static switch input.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Q601</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Manual
bypass switch (MBS)</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This
switch enables service or maintenance work. Two positions are available:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto:</b> in this position the load is supplied from the
system (inverter or static bypass)</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass:</b> in this position the load is supplied directly
from the bypass mains. The static switch is isolated from the bypass
mains. For a total isolation of the system part, Q001 and Q201 must
also be open.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">X601</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">System
output terminal (Load terminal)</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This
terminal provides for the connection of the load.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A801</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Interface
board</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Interface_Board_A801_REF_0000116986.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A802,A803</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Current
sense boards</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">These
boards contain the burden resistor for the appropriate current transformer.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A805,A806</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Voltage
sense boards</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">These
boards convert the acquired voltage via the interface board to a standard
value.</entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A810</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Human
Machine Interface (HMI)</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Human_Machine_Interface_A810_REF_0000117151.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A811</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">External
connection board</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_External_Connection_Board_A811_REF_0000103066.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A812</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Option:
Parallel connection board</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">This
board is installed if two units are connected in parallel. The board’s
functions are:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Communication between the individual units</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Load sharing between the individual units. Each unit takes
over the same proportional part of the load.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">E101E102E401E701</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Fan
system</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Consists
of:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">fans with internal hall sensor for monitoring of the rotation
speed</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">fan monitor for monitoring the rotation speed of each fan.
If the rotation speed falls below the threshold value an alarm is
generated</p>
                           </li>
                        </ul>See <xref href="Service_Power_Module_Ventilation_E101___E701_REF_0000103117.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/> and <xref href="Service_SBS_Ventilation_E401_REF_0000103065.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">A103A104</b>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">Capacitor boards</entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">See <xref href="Service_Capacitor_Board_A103___A104_REF_0000103190.dita"
                              format="dita"
                              scope="local"
                              type="reference"
                              class="- topic/xref "/>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </section>
